						<summary>

						<p>This records the gift of a golden hand-plate weighing 3(1/4) <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> and set with precious stones worth 2 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> and 2 <hi rend="italic">akkam</hi>, for being worn (on the palm) by the image of Āḍalviḍaṅgadēvar (Naṭarāja) in the temple at Tiruviḍaimarudil, made by a merchant of the place by name Kaḷari Tōṉṟi.</p>						

